FBIS3-28698 "dreas027_a_94039" FBIS-EAS-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Survey Shows Land Prices Continue To Fall OW0802123194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1118 GMT 8 Feb 94 OW0802123194 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 8 KYODO -- Land prices in Japan were continuing to fall as of January 1 due to Japan's prolonged economic slump, the National Land Agency said in a survey released Tuesday [8 February]. The agency made a spot survey on 849 sites in residential and commercial districts of both big and smaller cities, including Japan's major centers of Tokyo, Nagoya and Osaka. The survey is conducted once every three months. Of 522 residential tracts, prices on 88 were down substantially, an increase from the 81 recorded in the previous three-month-period survey, while prices on 163 fell slightly, down from 139, and prices on 264 remained flat, up from 258. Prices fell across the board on the 327 commercial sites.
